youtube.com/watch?v=8rvGR1hVIFw&list=PLFq2zv7d_8BDM_v72NSdA1Dg2IRjZuZrb\n\t\t\t- Frequency\n\t\t\t  collapsed:: true\n\t\t\t\t- Basic exercises\n\t\t\t\t\t- 2 sets of 5 breath cycles each morning and 1-2 sets, 5 reps each night\n\t\t\t\t- Weight based\n\t\t\t\t\t- min 2-3 times a week for 3-4 sets of 10-15 reps\n\t\t- Progression\n\t\t  https://www.conorharris.com/blog/how-to-progress-corrective-exercise-from-the-ground-to-upright\n\t\t  https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TZh4gflQC8o&t=2s\n\t\t\t- Referenced position\n\t\t\t\t- 90/90 hip lift\n\t\t\t\t\t- Basic\n\t\t\t\t\t\t- Execution\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t- https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=GYTsaqHgtRY&t=2s&pp=ygUfUFJJIDkwLzkwIEhpcCBMaWZ0IGNvbm9yIGhhcnJpcw%3D%3D\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t- Breathing\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t- https://youtu.be/rjcVYy7szAI?si=kn3Pa2YwdR5TgEyu\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t- Inhale through your nose, 5-10 sec exhale through mouth, pause for 5 seconds\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t- When you inhale, you should get a little bit taller. When you exhale, you should get a little bit shorter.\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t- Full exhalation is essential\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t- https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LlxtPicx6H8\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t- 4-6/10 harmstring contraction\n\t\t\t- Referenced position + muscle integration\n\t\t\t\t- 90/90 hip lift with hip shift\n\t\t\t\t\t- https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=YoSf3OFpPp4\n\t\t\t\t- Sitting exercise\n\t\t\t\t\t- https://youtu.be/uYtLHHT1AhU?t=382\n\t\t\t\t- Ab exercises\n\t\t\t\t\t- https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Uy4u23pzm3E&list=PLFq2zv7d_8BDM_v72NSdA1Dg2IRjZuZrb&index=13\n\t\t\t- Removing references + integration\n\t\t\t\t- Band exercises\n\t\t\t\t\t- https://youtu.be/xq0hXN5mAxY\n\t\t\t\t\t- https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=DGR_xH0wHrY&t=471s\n\t\t\t\t- Gait Mechanics\n\t\t\t\t\t- https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cnNZ8YSaq74&list=PLFq2zv7d_8BDM_v72NSdA1Dg2IRjZuZrb&index=15\n\t\t\t- Loaded integration\n\t\t\t\t- https://youtu.be/Tsa-NaWpPxY?si=C5ZDspIxBz-yHhGz\n\t\t\t\t- Loaded integration in [starting] upright position\n